  <!-- ═══ SECTION 7: DEFENCE LAYERS ═══ -->
  <section class="section" style="animation-delay: 0.4s;">
    <div class="section-label">Section 07</div>
    <h2>Defence Layers — Beyond Standard Quality Gates</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">
      Standard data platforms offer expectations, constraints, and quality rules. The Agentic ERP needs more,
      because the cost of a wrong NAV is asymmetric — a quiet error compounds into a restatement, a regulatory
      finding, and reputational damage. Six layers, executed in fail-fast order from cheapest to most expensive.
    </p>

    <div class="defence-grid">

      <div class="defence-card">
        <div class="defence-num">LAYER 01</div>
        <h4>Dual-Builder Consensus</h4>
        <p>Two independent LLMs from different model families generate the calculation. Both must produce identical output. N-version programming applied to AI generation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="defence-card">
        <div class="defence-num">LAYER 02</div>
        <h4>Tool Library Regression</h4>
        <p>Every new script is tested against the Tool Library of verified precedents. Known inputs must produce identical outputs. Drift is caught before execution.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="defence-card">
        <div class="defence-num">LAYER 03</div>
        <h4>Z3 Formal Verification</h4>
        <p>Microsoft's Z3 SMT solver mathematically proves invariants of the generated code. Pre/post-conditions derived from the Fund Rules Ontology. If the proof fails, execution stops.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="defence-card">
        <div class="defence-num">LAYER 04</div>
        <h4>Inverse Verification</h4>
        <p>An independent LLM (Auditor) reads the generated code and produces a plain-English explanation. The reviewer reads the explanation, not the code. Cross-referenced against the Ontology.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="defence-card">
        <div class="defence-num">LAYER 05</div>
        <h4>Property-Based Testing</h4>
        <p>Hypothesis generates 1000+ randomised inputs. Mathematical invariants must hold across the whole input space: fees ≥ 0, fees ≤ LPA max, NAV components sum correctly, and so on.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="defence-card">
        <div class="defence-num">LAYER 06</div>
        <h4>Novelty Gate</h4>
        <p>First-time calculation types always require human review, regardless of all automated verification. The Tool Library is only populated after explicit human validation. No silent firsts.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

